    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "`ListView` is technically unable to determine the expected `contentHeight` due to dynamic loading of delegates and different delegate heights. Also, our chats have too different items (some small, some too height) and approximation made by ListView components does not work well for our case.\r\nThis results in this terrible user experience: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3fC1lzTHP_0\r\n\r\nOne simple solution to this problem is to use cacheBuffer property: https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qml-qtquick-listview.html#cacheBuffer-prop\r\nWhen I tried to set this to 5000 (ad hoc value), this made all scrolling working smooth, but at the price of extra memory usage (+50Mb for chat in my case).\r\nThe more complex solution would it be to do the same as Discord does: try to scroll #random by holding and moving the scrollbar handle to the top. This will require some coding...\r\n\r\nOpened discussion in #random to brainstorm this further.",
